textBox.richText: This is a pretty good song. I actually never listened to it when I first got the album because it was part of a FREE DOWNLOAD bundle that came with the CD. Another song came with it; it was a remix of Schizophrenia which deeply frightens me with how much it deviates from the ever-so catchy beat of the NormalVersion. But yes, I tried incorporating these songs into the main album on iTunes which decided to give me a HARD TIME ABOUT IT so I gave up and made them a separate off-shoot album deale-o, but having the same album appear twice in my library irked me after a while so I got rid of the scaryremix and put just this song at the end of the normal album. Wasn’t that a nice little story? ˙sǝʎ :ɹǝʍsuɐ So anyway, I’m trying out making the line-spacing a bit larger. Does it improve readability?!? (Y/N) *note: answer is the same as the previous hidden answer. Edit: Apparently QuickTime audio files won’t load correctly in Safari for some reason. No one in the world is able to deduce the reason (I’m serious). And this only applies to “recent” things published (i.e., the last two songs to be published here won’t load in Safari while the rest will. Yeah, idfk either). So if some things won’t load, then I am quite sorry. …Although the number of people who read this site and use Macs and Safari are pretty slim anyway. If you really, really want to listen to some “fresh beats,” then go download Google Chrome and listen to them there. This is in no way a shameful plug for Google Chrome. Ricky would also be very proud of me, despite this not being a shameful plug like I previously stated.
